cast_shell: bind IPv4 loopback for page DevTools

The default IPv6AllZeros dual-stack bind silently leaves the http
handler thread without an accept loop on this kernel/glibc
combination: content/'s DevTools handler logs "Cannot start http
server" and the LISTEN socket sits unanswered.

Chromium >= M111 enforces localhost-only for /json/* anyway, so an
IPv4 localhost bind is functionally equivalent for our use case and
reliably serves CDP requests through the SSH tunnel from the host.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [kiosk-specific use case]

Signed-off-by: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>

--- a/chromecast/browser/devtools/remote_debugging_server.cc
+++ b/chromecast/browser/devtools/remote_debugging_server.cc
@@ -118,7 +118,12 @@
   return std::unique_ptr<content::DevToolsSocketFactory>(
       new UnixDomainServerSocketFactory(socket_name));
 #else
-  net::IPEndPoint endpoint(net::IPAddress::IPv6AllZeros(), port);
+  // bridgething patch: bind IPv4 loopback only. The original IPv6AllZeros
+  // dual-stack bind silently leaves the http handler thread without an
+  // accept loop on this kernel/glibc combination (content/'s DevTools
+  // handler logs "Cannot start http server" and the LISTEN socket sits
+  // unanswered). Chromium ≥ M111 enforces localhost-only for /json/* anyway.
+  net::IPEndPoint endpoint(net::IPAddress::IPv4Localhost(), port);
   return std::unique_ptr<content::DevToolsSocketFactory>(
       new TCPServerSocketFactory(endpoint));
 #endif
